OL,5,Ccomments
OL,7,FManchester United Muslim Supporters
OL,8,FClub said they are deeply concerned by
OL,9,FSir Jim's language, which they say
OL,10,Fechoes "frequently used in far-right
OL,11,Fnarratives that frame migrants as
OL,12,Finvaders and demographic threats".
OL,14,FMeanwhile, the UK's leading anti-
OL,15,Fracism educational charity, Show
OL,16,FRacism the Red Card, said: "Language
OL,17,Fof this kind echoes narratives that
OL,18,Fhave historically been used to
OL,19,Fstigmatise migrant communities, fuel
OL,20,Fdivision, and legitimise hostility
OL,21,Ftoward minority groups.
